  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are probing question that you will ask to the user for buying an AC?",
  "response": "When helping someone decide on purchasing an air conditioner, it's essential to understand their specific needs and situation. Here are some probing questions that can guide the conversation:\n\n1. **Room Size and Layout:**\n   - What is the square footage of the room or area you want to cool?\n   - Is the space open or divided by walls?\n\n2. **Budget:**\n   - What is your budget range for this purchase?\n   - Are you looking for an energy-efficient model to save on electricity bills in the long term?\n\n3. **Type of AC:**\n   - Are you considering a window unit, portable, split, or central air conditioning system?\n   - Do you have any preferences regarding specific brands or models?\n\n4. **Usage:**\n   - How many hours a day do you plan to use the AC?\n   - Is it for residential use, an office, or a commercial space?\n\n5. **Existing Infrastructure:**\n   - Do you have ductwork in place if considering a central AC system?\n   - Are there any size or location constraints for installing the unit?\n\n6. **Climate and Environment:**\n   - Do you live in a particularly hot and humid area, or is it more dry and warm?\n   - Are there any environmental concerns you'd like to address, such as reducing carbon footprint?\n\n7. **Features:**\n   - Are there any particular features you're looking for, such as smart technology, air purification, or dehumidification?\n   - How important is a quiet operation to you?\n\n8. **Seasonal Needs:**\n   - Do you need a unit that can provide both cooling in the summer and heating in the winter?\n   - How many months out of the year do you anticipate needing to use the air conditioner?\n\n9. **Installation:**\n   - Do you require professional installation, or are you comfortable with a DIY setup?\n   - Are there any restrictions or guidelines (such as in an apartment building) regarding installation?\n\n10. **Long-term Considerations:**\n    - Are you looking for a model with a good warranty and easy maintenance?\n    - How often do you plan to maintain or clean the unit?\n\nThese questions can help narrow down the options and find the best air conditioning solution tailored to the user's specific needs and preferences.",
